This paper is about kinodynamic planning, which involves planning the motion of a robot subject to dynamic constraints. The paper proposes a new approach to solving this problem using co-learning and indirect optimal control. The paper also mentions the use of supervised learning and the reduction of computational effort, which are common themes in machine learning and robotics research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
